Database
Too much load - replicate database
one database for write, multiple databases for read
sych lag in replication db, consistent
They were set up to handle all read traffic and logic was built to know when it was safe (consistent) to read from a replica versus the main master DB.

Too much data - sharding
range query

Load Balancer - It provides the ability to scale your app.
High availability - which means your system is always online.
    eg. if server A is down, server B will switch it and user does't
    notice anything.

vertical scaling - throw more CPUs and memory